	<Title>
		Add flax to your diet
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Never heard of flaxseed? Flaxseed is the seed of the flax plant, and it can give you a big nutritional boost. Flaxseed is high in fiber, omega-3 fatty acids and phytochemicals. It can help reduce total blood cholesterol and low-density lipoprotein (LDL), which may reduce your heart disease risk. Add a tablespoon to your daily diet. Buy whole, raw flaxseed at your local grocery or health food store and grind it in a coffee grinder, or buy pre-ground flaxseed. Add flaxseed to your cereal, oatmeal or yogurt, or mix into cookies, muffins and other baked goods.&lt;/p&gt;
